-----|------------|\n66: | Phase 1: Foundation | T1.1 | Pending | 0% |\n67: \n68: **Total Progress: 0% Complete**\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## References\n73: \n74: - Design: `changes/AR-032/design.md`\n75: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md`\n76: - Proposal: `changes/AR-032/proposal.md`\n\n(End of file - total 76 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images) |\n| Module | `docker` |\n| Language | Dockerfile |\n| Size | S |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 pending] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Foundation (ST-1)\n\n- [ ] **T1.1**: [TO BE FILLED: Task description]\n  - Purpose: [TO BE FILLED]","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775886397824,"end":1775886397846}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886397851,"sessionID":"ses_284ec6c0effeuVBVVdzk4kiXnu","part":{"id":"prt_d7b13ed660016qzVZdvqc3JYBn","messageID":"msg_d7b13bf0e001UrUjBp9Isrk1O8","sessionID":"ses_284ec6c0effeuVBVVdzk4kiXnu","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-1774703e3aab445dafcfc67c6cf90ef9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images) |\n8: | Module | `docker` |\n9: | Language | Dockerfile |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 (completed) |\n12: \n13: Multi-stage Dockerfile patterns for AgentCube's three core container images, optimizing for build separation, security, build efficiency, and consistency across workloadmanager, router, and picod images.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### High-Level Architecture\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n23: │                          Docker Multi-Stage Build Pipeline                        │\n24: ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n25: │                                                                                   │\n26: │   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n27: │   │                        Source Repository (Context)                       │   │\n28: │   │   go.mod, go.sum, cmd/, pkg/, client-go/                                 │   │\n29: │   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n30: │                                    │                                              │\n31: │                                    ▼                                              │\n32: │   ┌────────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────┐       │\n33: │   │ docker/Dockerfile  │  │docker/Dockerfile.  │  │docker/Dockerfile.  │       │\n34: │   │                    │  │      router        │  │      picod         │       │\n35: │   └────────────────────┘  └────────────────────┘  └────────────────────┘       │\n36: │            │                       │                        │                    │\n37: │            ▼                       ▼                        ▼                    │\n38: │   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n39: │   │                        Stage 1: Builder                                  │   │\n40: │   │   FROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder                                     │   │\n41: │   │   ├─ WORKDIR /app                                                        │   │\n42: │   │   ├─ COPY go.mod go.sum ./                                               │   │\n43: │   │   ├─ RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/go/pkg/mod go mod download          │   │\n44: │   │   ├─ COPY . .                                                            │   │\n45: │   │   ├─ ENV CGO_ENABLED=0                                                   │   │\n46: │   │   ├─ RUN go build -ldflags=\"-w -s\" -o /app/bin/<binary> ./cmd/<module>   │   │\n47: │   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n48: │                                    │                                              │\n49: │                                    ▼                                              │\n50: │   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n51: │   │                        Stage 2: Runtime                                  │   │\n52: │   │   FROM alpine:3.19 / ubuntu:24.04                                        │   │\n53: │   │   ├─ RUN apk add --no-cache ca-certificates                             │   │\n54: │   │   ├─ RUN adduser -D -u 1000 <user>  (Alpine only)                       │   │\n55: │   │   ├─ COPY --from=builder /app/bin/<binary> /app/bin/<binary>            │   │\n56: │   │   ├─ USER 1000 / root                                                    │   │\n57: │   │   ├─ EXPOSE 8080                                                         │   │\n58: │   │   ├─ ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/bin/<binary>\"]                                   │   │\n59: │   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n60: │                                    │                                              │\n61: │                                    ▼                                              │\n62: │   ┌────────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────┐       │\n63: │   │ workloadmanager    │  │     router        │  │      picod         │       │\n64: │   │    image (~20MB)   │  │   image (~20MB)   │  │   image (~50MB)    │       │\n65: │   │    UID: 1000       │  │    UID: 1000      │  │    UID: root       │       │\n66: │   └────────────────────┘  └────────────────────┘  └────────────────────┘       │\n67: │                                                                                   │\n68: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n69: ```\n70: \n71: ### Image Target Summary\n72: \n73: | Image | Binary | Runtime Base | User | Size Target |\n74: |-------|--------|--------------|------|-------------|\n75: | `workloadmanager` | `./cmd/workload-manager` | `alpine:3.19` | `apiserver` (UID 1000) | <50MB |\n76: | `agentcube-router` | `./cmd/router` | `alpine:3.19` | `router` (UID 1000) | <50MB |\n77: | `picod` | `./cmd/picod` | `ubuntu:24.04` | `root` (sandbox permissions) | <100MB |\n78: \n79: ### Build Pipeline Flow\n80: \n81: ```\n82: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n83: │                        Makefile Build Targets                                │\n84: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n85: │                                                                              │\n86: │   make docker-build                                                          │\n87: │        │                                                                     │\n88: │        ▼                                                                     │\n89: │   docker build -f docker/Dockerfile                                          │\n90: │        -t $(IMAGE_REPO)/workloadmanager:$(VERSION)                           │\n91: │        --build-arg TARGETOS=linux                                            │\n92: │        --build-arg TARGETARCH=amd64                                          │\n93: │        .                                                                     │\n94: │                                                                              │\n95: │   make docker-build-router                                                   │\n96: │        │                                                                     │\n97: │        ▼                                                                     │\n98: │   docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router                                   │\n99: │        -t $(IMAGE_REPO)/router:$(VERSION)                                    │\n100: │        .                                                                     │\n101: │                                                                              │\n102: │   make docker-build-picod                                                    │\n103: │        │                                                                     │\n104: │        ▼                                                                     │\n105: │   docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.picod                                    │\n106: │        -t $(IMAGE_REPO)/picod:$(VERSION)                                     │\n107: │        .                                                                     │\n108: │                                                                              │\n109: │   make docker-build-all                                                      │\n110: │        │                                                                     │\n111: │        ├─► docker-build                                                      │\n112: │        ├─► docker-build-router                                               │\n113: │        └─► docker-build-picod                                                │\n114: │                                                                              │\n115: │   make docker-buildx-push-*                                                  │\n116: │        │                                                                     │\n117: │        ▼                                                                     │\n118: │   docker buildx build --platform linux/amd64,arm64                           │\n119: │        --push -t ghcr.io/...                                                 │\n120: │                                                                              │\n121: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n122: ```\n123: \n124: ### Component Relationships\n125: \n126: ```\n127: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n128: │                          Deployment Architecture                               │\n129: ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n130: │                                                                               │\n131: │   ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n132: │   │                     Kubernetes Cluster                                  │  │\n133: │   │                                                                        │  │\n134: │   │   ┌─────────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────┐                  │  │\n135: │   │   │ router Deployment   │    │workloadmanager      │                  │  │\n136: │   │   │ ┌─────────────────┐ │    │ Deployment          │                  │  │\n137: │   │   │ │  router image   │ │    │ ┌─────────────────┐ │                  │  │\n138: │   │   │ │  alpine:3.19    │ │    │ │workloadmanager  │ │                  │  │\n139: │   │   │ │  UID: 1000      │ │    │ │  image          │ │                  │  │\n140: │   │   │ │  :8080          │ │    │ │  alpine:3.19    │ │                  │  │\n141: │   │   │ └─────────────────┘ │    │ │  UID: 1000      │ │                  │  │\n142: │   │   └─────────────────────┘    │ │  :8080          │ │                  │  │\n143: │   │                               │ └─────────────────┘ │                  │  │\n144: │   │                               └─────────────────────┘                  │  │\n145: │   │                                                                        │  │\n146: │   │   ┌─────────────────────┐                                             │  │\n147: │   │   │ Sandbox Pod         │                                             │  │\n148: │   │   │ ┌─────────────────┐ │                                             │  │\n149: │   │   │ │  picod sidecar  │ │                                             │  │\n150: │   │   │ │  ubuntu:24.04   │ │                                             │  │\n151: │   │   │ │  root user      │ │                                             │  │\n152: │   │   │ │  :8080          │ │                                             │  │\n153: │   │   │ └─────────────────┘ │                                             │  │\n154: │   │   └─────────────────────┘                                             │  │\n155: │   │                                                                        │  │\n156: │   └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n157: │                                                                               │\n158: │   ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n159: │   │                       CI/CD Pipeline                                    │  │\n160: │   │                                                                        │  │\n161: │   │   GitHub Actions                                                        │  │\n162: │   │       │                                                                 │  │\n163: │   │       ├─► main.yml: make docker-build                                   │  │\n164: │   │       ├─► build-push-release.yml: make docker-buildx-push-*            │  │\n165: │   │       ├─► E2E: run_e2e.sh                                              │  │\n166: │   │       │       └─► make docker-build-all                                │  │\n167: │   │       │       └─► kind load docker-image                                │  │\n168: │   │                                                                        │  │\n169: │   └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n170: │                                                                               │\n171: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n172: ```\n173: \n174: ---\n175: \n176: ## Data Structures\n177: \n178: ### Dockerfile Stage Structure\n179: \n180: #### Workload Manager Dockerfile (`docker/Dockerfile`)\n181: \n182: ```dockerfile\n183: # Stage 1: Builder\n184: FROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\n185: \n186: WORKDIR /app\n187: \n188: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n189: RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/go/pkg/mod \\\n190:     go mod download\n191: \n192: COPY . .\n193: \n194: ENV CGO_ENABLED=0\n195: ENV GOOS=linux\n196: ENV GOARCH=amd64\n197: \n198: RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache/go-build \\\n199:     go build -ldflags=\"-w -s\" -o /app/bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n200: \n201: # Stage 2: Runtime\n202: FROM alpine:3.19\n203: \n204: RUN apk add --no-cache ca-certificates tzdata\n205: \n206: RUN adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver\n207: \n208: WORKDIR /app\n209: \n210: COPY --from=builder /app/bin/workloadmanager /app/bin/workloadmanager\n211: \n212: USER 1000\n213: \n214: EXPOSE 8080\n215: \n216: ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/bin/workloadmanager\"]\n217: ```\n218: \n219: #### Router Dockerfile (`docker/Dockerfile.router`)\n220: \n221: ```dockerfile\n222: # Stage 1: Builder\n223: FROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\n224: \n225: WORKDIR /app\n226: \n227: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n228: RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/go/pkg/mod \\\n229:     go mod download\n230: \n231: COPY . .\n232: COPY client-go/ client-go/\n233: \n234: ENV CGO_ENABLED=0\n235: ENV GOOS=linux\n236: ENV GOARCH=amd64\n237: \n238: RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache/go-build \\\n239:     go build -ldflags=\"-w -s\" -o /app/bin/router ./cmd/router\n240: \n241: # Stage 2: Runtime\n242: FROM alpine:3.19\n243: \n244: RUN apk add --no-cache ca-certificates tzdata\n245: \n246: RUN adduser -D -u 1000 router\n247: \n248: WORKDIR /app\n249: \n250: COPY --from=builder /app/bin/router /app/bin/router\n251: \n252: USER 1000\n253: \n254: EXPOSE 8080\n255: \n256: ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/bin/router\"]\n257: ```\n258: \n259: #### PicoD Dockerfile (`docker/Dockerfile.picod`)\n260: \n261: ```dockerfile\n262: # Stage 1: Builder\n263: FROM golang:1.24 AS builder\n264: \n265: WORKDIR /app\n266: \n267: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n268: RUN go mod download\n269: \n270: COPY . .\n271: \n272: ENV CGO_ENABLED=0\n273: ENV GOOS=linux\n274: ENV GOARCH=amd64\n275: \n276: RUN go build -ldflags=\"-w -s\" -o /app/bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n277: \n278: # Stage 2: Runtime\n279: FROM ubuntu:24.04\n280: \n281: RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \\\n282:     python3 \\\n283:     python3-pip \\\n284:     ca-certificates \\\n285:     && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n286: \n287: WORKDIR /app\n288: \n289: COPY --from=builder /app/bin/picod /app/bin/picod\n290: \n291: EXPOSE 8080\n292: \n293: ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/bin/picod\"]\n294: ```\n295: \n296: ### Dockerfile Stage Data Model\n297: \n298: ```yaml\n299: StageDefinition:\n300:   builder:\n301:     base_image: \"golang:1.24-alpine\"\n302:     workdir: \"/app\"\n303:     env_vars:\n304:       CGO_ENABLED: \"0\"\n305:       GOOS: \"${TARGETOS:-linux}\"\n306:       GOARCH: \"${TARGETARCH:-amd64}\"\n307:     cache_mounts:\n308:       - target: \"/go/pkg/mod\"\n309:         type: \"cache\"\n310:         key: \"go-mod-cache\"\n311:       - target: \"/root/.cache/go-build\"\n312:         type: \"cache\"\n313:         key: \"go-build-cache\"\n314:     operations:\n315:       - copy: [\"go.mod\", \"go.sum\", \"./\"]\n316:       - run: \"go mod download\"\n317:       - copy: \".\"\n318:       - build: \"./cmd/<module> -> /app/bin/<binary>\"\n319:     build_flags:\n320:       ldflags: \"-w -s\"\n321:       trimpath: true\n322: \n323:   runtime:\n324:     base_image_alpine: \"alpine:3.19\"\n325:     base_image_ubuntu: \"ubuntu:24.04\"\n326:     packages_alpine:\n327:       - \"ca-certificates\"\n328:       - \"tzdata\"\n329:     packages_ubuntu:\n330:       - \"python3\"\n331:       - \"python3-pip\"\n332:       - \"ca-certificates\"\n333:     user:\n334:       alpine:\n335:         name: \"<service_user>\"\n336:         uid: 1000\n337:         create_command: \"adduser -D -u 1000 <user>\"\n338:       ubuntu:\n339:         name: \"root\"\n340:         uid: 0\n341:     operations:\n342:       - copy_from: \"builder:/app/bin/<binary> -> /app/bin/<binary>\"\n343:       - expose: 8080\n344:       - entrypoint: \"/app/bin/<binary>\"\n345: ```\n346: \n347: ### Build Arguments Schema\n348: \n349: ```yaml\n350: BuildArgs:\n351:   TARGETOS:\n352:     type: string\n353:     default: \"linux\"\n354:     values: [\"linux\", \"windows\", \"darwin\"]\n355:     description: \"Target operating system for cross-compilation\"\n356:     \n357:   TARGETARCH:\n358:     type: string\n359:     default: \"amd64\"\n360:     values: [\"amd64\", \"arm64\", \"arm\", \"386\"]\n361:     description: \"Target architecture for cross-compilation\"\n362:     \n363:   VERSION:\n364:     type: string\n365:     default: \"latest\"\n366:     description: \"Image tag version\"\n367:     \n368:   IMAGE_REPO:\n369:     type: string\n370:     default: \"ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube\"\n371:     description: \"Image repository base URL\"\n372: ```\n373: \n374: ---\n375: \n376: ## API Contracts\n377: \n378: ### Makefile Target Contract\n379: \n380: ```makefile\n381: # Image naming convention\n382: IMAGE_REPO ?= ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube\n383: VERSION ?= $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty)\n384: \n385: # Build targets\n386: .PHONY: docker-build docker-build-router docker-build-picod docker-build-all\n387: \n388: docker-build:\n389: \tdocker build \\\n390: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile \\\n391: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/workloadmanager:$(VERSION) \\\n392: \t\t--build-arg TARGETOS=linux \\\n393: \t\t--build-arg TARGETARCH=amd64 \\\n394: \t\t.\n395: \n396: docker-build-router:\n397: \tdocker build \\\n398: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.router \\\n399: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/router:$(VERSION) \\\n400: \t\t--build-arg TARGETOS=linux \\\n401: \t\t--build-arg TARGETARCH=amd64 \\\n402: \t\t.\n403: \n404: docker-build-picod:\n405: \tdocker build \\\n406: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.picod \\\n407: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/picod:$(VERSION) \\\n408: \t\t.\n409: \n410: docker-build-all: docker-build docker-build-router docker-build-picod\n411: \n412: # Multi-arch buildx targets\n413: .PHONY: docker-buildx-push docker-buildx-push-router docker-buildx-push-picod\n414: \n415: docker-buildx-push:\n416: \tdocker buildx build \\\n417: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile \\\n418: \t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n419: \t\t--build-arg TARGETOS=linux \\\n420: \t\t--build-arg TARGETARCH=amd64 \\\n421: \t\t--push \\\n422: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/workloadmanager:$(VERSION) \\\n423: \t\t.\n424: \n425: docker-buildx-push-router:\n426: \tdocker buildx build \\\n427: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.router \\\n428: \t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n429: \t\t--push \\\n430: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/router:$(VERSION) \\\n431: \t\t.\n432: \n433: docker-buildx-push-picod:\n434: \tdocker buildx build \\\n435: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.picod \\\n436: \t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n437: \t\t--push \\\n438: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/picod:$(VERSION) \\\n439: \t\t.\n440: ```\n441: \n442: ### Docker Build Command Interface\n443: \n444: ```yaml\n445: DockerBuildCommand:\n446:   parameters:\n447:     dockerfile:\n448:       type: string\n449:       required: true\n450:       values: [\"docker/Dockerfile\", \"docker/Dockerfile.router\", \"docker/Dockerfile.picod\"]\n451:     tag:\n452:       type: string\n453:       required: true\n454:       pattern: \"${IMAGE_REPO}/${IMAGE_NAME}:${VERSION}\"\n455:     context:\n456:       type: string\n457:       default: \".\"\n458:       description: \"Build context directory (repository root)\"\n459:     build_args:\n460:       TARGETOS:\n461:         type: string\n462:         optional: true\n463:       TARGETARCH:\n464:         type: string\n465:         optional: true\n466:     platform:\n467:       type: string\n468:       optional: true\n469:       pattern: \"linux/amd64,linux/arm64\"\n470:       description: \"Multi-arch platform specification\"\n471: \n472:   outputs:\n473:     image_id:\n474:       type: string\n475:       description: \"Built image SHA256 digest\"\n476:     image_size:\n477:       type: integer\n478:       unit: \"bytes\"\n479:       description: \"Final image size\"\n480:     layers:\n481:       type: integer\n482:       description: \"Number of layers in final image\"\n483: ```\n484: \n485: ### Helm Values Contract\n486: \n487: ```yaml\n488: # manifests/charts/base/values.yaml\n489: images:\n490:   workloadmanager:\n491:     repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube/workloadmanager\n492:     tag: latest\n493:     pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n494:     \n495:   router:\n496:     repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube/router\n497:     tag: latest\n498:     pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n499:     \n500:   picod:\n501:     repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube/picod\n502:     tag: latest\n503:     pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n504: ```\n505: \n506: ---\n507: \n508: ## Error Handling\n509: \n510: ### Build Error Categories\n511: \n512: | Error Category | Description | Detection | Recovery Action |\n513: |----------------|-------------|-----------|-----------------|\n514: | `BuildArgError` | Invalid/missing build arguments | Docker build start | Validate args before build |\n515: | `CopyError` | Source file not found in context | `COPY` instruction | Check file existence in context |\n516: | `GoBuildError` | Go compilation failure | `go build` command | Review compilation logs, fix source |\n517: | `ModDownloadError` | Go module download failure | `go mod download` | Check network, verify go.mod |\n518: | `UserCreateError` | Non-root user creation failure | `adduser` command | Alpine package availability |\n519: | `CacheMountError` | BuildKit cache mount failure | `--mount=type=cache` | Enable BuildKit (`DOCKER_BUILDKIT=1`) |\n520: | `ImagePullError` | Base image pull failure | `FROM` instruction | Check registry connectivity |\n521: | `CrossArchError` | Cross-architecture compilation failure | `TARGETARCH` mismatch | Verify Go cross-compilation support |\n522: \n523: ### Build Failure Handling Pattern\n524: \n525: ```bash\n526: #!/bin/bash\n527: # build-with-error-handling.sh\n528: \n529: set -euo pipefail\n530: \n531: build_image() {\n532:     local dockerfile=\"$1\"\n533:     local tag=\"$2\"\n534:     \n535:     echo \"Building image from $dockerfile...\"\n536:     \n537:     if ! docker build -f \"$dockerfile\" -t \"$tag\" .; then\n538:         echo \"ERROR: Build failed for $dockerfile\"\n539:         \n540:         docker build -f \"$dockerfile\" -t \"$tag\" . --no-cache\n541:         \n542:         if ! docker build -f \"$dockerfile\" -t \"$tag\" . --no-cache; then\n543:             echo \"ERROR: Build failed even with --no-cache\"\n544:             return 1\n545:         fi\n546:     fi\n547:     \n548:     local image_size=$(docker image inspect \"$tag\" --format='{{.Size}}')\n549:     echo \"Image size: $(numfmt --to=iec $image_size)\"\n550:     \n551:     if [[ $image_size -gt 100000000 ]]; then\n552:         echo \"WARNING: Image exceeds 100MB size target\"\n553:     fi\n554:     \n555:     return 0\n556: }\n557: \n558: main() {\n559:     local failed=0\n560:     \n561:     for image in workloadmanager router picod; do\n562:         local dockerfile=\"docker/Dockerfile\"\n563:         if [[ \"$image\" != \"workloadmanager\" ]]; then\n564:             dockerfile=\"docker/Dockerfile.$image\"\n565:         fi\n566:         \n567:         if ! build_image \"$dockerfile\" \"agentcube/$image:test\"; then\n568:             failed=1\n569:         fi\n570:     done\n571:     \n572:     if [[ $failed -eq 1 ]]; then\n573:         echo \"ERROR: One or more builds failed\"\n574:         exit 1\n575:     fi\n576:     \n577:     echo \"All builds completed successfully\"\n578: }\n579: \n580: main \"$@\"\n581: ```\n582: \n583: ### Runtime Error Detection\n584: \n585: | Error | Detection | Container Behavior | Remediation |\n586: |-------|-----------|-------------------|-------------|\n587: | `EntrypointNotFound` | Binary not in expected path | Container exits immediately | Verify COPY instruction |\n588: | `PermissionDenied` | UID lacks execute permission | Exit code 126 | Check USER directive |\n589: | `PortBindFailed` | Port 8080 already bound | Container exits with error | Check port conflicts |\n590: | `MissingDependency` | Required package not installed | Binary execution fails | Verify RUN apk/apt install |\n591: \n592: ### Health Check Contract\n593: \n594: ```dockerfile\n595: # Optional health check for runtime stage\n596: HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=10s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \\\n597:     CMD wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1\n598: ```\n599: \n600: ---\n601: \n602: ## Testing Strategy\n603: \n604: ### Test Categories\n605: \n606: | Category | Scope | Tools | Purpose |\n607: |----------|-------|-------|---------|\n608: | Dockerfile Syntax | Dockerfile validity | `docker build --check`, `hadolint` | Validate Dockerfile syntax and best practices |\n609: | Build Execution | Full build process | `docker build`, `make docker-build-*` | Verify images build successfully |\n610: | Image Size | Runtime image size | `docker image inspect`, size comparison | Ensure size targets met (<50MB Alpine, <100MB Ubuntu) |\n611: | Runtime Execution | Container startup | `docker run`, health checks | Verify container runs correctly |\n612: | Security Scan | Vulnerability detection | `trivy`, `docker scout` | Identify CVEs in base images |\n613: | User Isolation | Non-root execution | `docker exec`, UID check | Verify security context |\n614: | Cross-Arch | Multi-arch builds | `docker buildx`, Kind cluster | Test amd64/arm64 builds |\n615: | E2E Integration | Full deployment | Kind, Helm, E2E tests | Verify images work in cluster |\n616: \n617: ### Unit Tests: Dockerfile Syntax\n618: \n619: ```bash\n620: #!/bin/bash\n621: # test_dockerfile_syntax.sh\n622: \n623: test_dockerfile_exists() {\n624:     for dockerfile in docker/Dockerfile docker/Dockerfile.router docker/Dockerfile.picod; do\n625:         if [[ ! -f \"$dockerfile\" ]]; then\n626:             echo \"FAIL: $dockerfile does not exist\"\n627:             return 1\n628:         fi\n629:         echo \"PASS: $dockerfile exists\"\n630:     done\n631:     return 0\n632: }\n633: \n634: test_builder_base_image() {\n635:     for dockerfile in docker/Dockerfile docker/Dockerfile.router; do\n636:         if ! grep -q \"FROM golang:1.24\" \"$dockerfile\"; then\n637:             echo \"FAIL: $dockerfile missing golang:1.24 builder\"\n638:             return 1\n639:         fi\n640:         echo \"PASS: $dockerfile has correct builder base\"\n641:     done\n642:     return 0\n643: }\n644: \n645: test_runtime_base_image() {\n646:     local expected_base=\"alpine:3.19\"\n647:     \n648:     for dockerfile in docker/Dockerfile docker/Dockerfile.router; do\n649:         if ! grep -q \"FROM $expected_base\" \"$dockerfile\"; then\n650:             echo \"FAIL: $dockerfile missing $expected_base runtime\"\n651:             return 1\n652:         fi\n653:         echo \"PASS: $dockerfile has Alpine runtime base\"\n654:     done\n655:     \n656:     if ! grep -q \"FROM ubuntu:24.04\" docker/Dockerfile.picod; then\n657:         echo \"FAIL: docker/Dockerfile.picod missing ubuntu:24.04 runtime\"\n658:         return 1\n659:     fi\n660:     echo \"PASS: docker/Dockerfile.picod has Ubuntu runtime base\"\n661:     \n662:     return 0\n663: }\n664: \n665: test_cgo_disabled() {\n666:     for dockerfile in docker/Dockerfile docker/Dockerfile.router docker/Dockerfile.picod; do\n667:         if ! grep -q \"CGO_ENABLED=0\" \"$dockerfile\"; then\n668:             echo \"FAIL: $dockerfile missing CGO_ENABLED=0\"\n669:             return 1\n670:         fi\n671:         echo \"PASS: $dockerfile has CGO_ENABLED=0\"\n672:     done\n673:     return 0\n674: }\n675: \n676: test_non_root_user() {\n677:     for dockerfile in docker/Dockerfile docker/Dockerfile.router; do\n678:         if ! grep -q \"USER 1000\" \"$dockerfile\"; then\n679:             echo \"FAIL: $dockerfile missing USER 1000\"\n680:             return 1\n681:         fi\n682:         echo \"PASS: $dockerfile has non-root user directive\"\n683:     done\n684:     \n685:     if grep -q \"USER 1000\" docker/Dockerfile.picod; then\n686:         echo \"FAIL: docker/Dockerfile.picod should NOT have USER 1000\"\n687:         return 1\n688:     fi\n689:     echo \"PASS: docker/Dockerfile.picod runs as root (expected)\"\n690:     \n691:     return 0\n692: }\n693: \n694: test_ldflags_optimization() {\n695:     for dockerfile in docker/Dockerfile docker/Dockerfile.router docker/Dockerfile.picod; do\n696:         if ! grep -q 'ldflags=\"-w -s\"' \"$dockerfile\"; then\n697:             echo \"FAIL: $dockerfile missing -ldflags=\\\"-w -s\\\"\"\n698:             return 1\n699:         fi\n700:         echo \"PASS: $dockerfile has binary optimization ldflags\"\n701:     done\n702:     return 0\n703: }\n704: \n705: main() {\n706:     local failed=0\n707:     \n708:     test_dockerfile_exists || failed=1\n709:     test_builder_base_image || failed=1\n710:     test_runtime_base_image || failed=1\n711:     test_cgo_disabled || failed=1\n712:     test_non_root_user || failed=1\n713:     test_ldflags_optimization || failed=1\n714:     \n715:     if [[ $failed -eq 1 ]]; then\n716:         echo \"TESTS FAILED\"\n717:         exit 1\n718:     fi\n719:     \n720:     echo \"ALL TESTS PASSED\"\n721:     exit 0\n722: }\n723: \n724: main\n725: ```\n726: \n727: ### Integration Tests: Build Execution\n728: \n729: ```bash\n730: #!/bin/bash\n731: # test_docker_build.sh\n732: \n733: set -euo pipefail\n734: \n735: cleanup() {\n736:     docker rmi -f agentcube-test-workloadmanager agentcube-test-router agentcube-test-picod 2>/dev/null || true\n737: }\n738: \n739: trap cleanup EXIT\n740: \n741: test_workloadmanager_build() {\n742:     echo \"Testing workloadmanager build...\"\n743:     \n744:     if ! docker build -f docker/Dockerfile -t agentcube-test-workloadmanager .; then\n745:         echo \"FAIL: workloadmanager build failed\"\n746:         return 1\n747:     fi\n748:     \n749:     local size=$(docker image inspect agentcube-test-workloadmanager --format='{{.Size}}')\n750:     if [[ $size -gt 50000000 ]]; then\n751:         echo \"FAIL: workloadmanager image exceeds 50MB: $(numfmt --to=iec $size)\"\n752:         return 1\n753:     fi\n754:     \n755:     echo \"PASS: workloadmanager build succeeded, size: $(numfmt --to=iec $size)\"\n756:     return 0\n757: }\n758: \n759: test_router_build() {\n760:     echo \"Testing router build...\"\n761:     \n762:     if ! docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t agentcube-test-router .; then\n763:         echo \"FAIL: router build failed\"\n764:         return 1\n765:     fi\n766:     \n767:     local size=$(docker image inspect agentcube-test-router --format='{{.Size}}')\n768:     if [[ $size -gt 50000000 ]]; then\n769:         echo \"FAIL: router image exceeds 50MB: $(numfmt --to=iec $size)\"\n770:         return 1\n771:     fi\n772:     \n773:     echo \"PASS: router build succeeded, size: $(numfmt --to=iec $size)\"\n774:     return 0\n775: }\n776: \n777: test_picod_build() {\n778:     echo \"Testing picod build...\"\n779:     \n780:     if ! docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.picod -t agentcube-test-picod .; then\n781:         echo \"FAIL: picod build failed\"\n782:         return 1\n783:     fi\n784:     \n785:     local size=$(docker image inspect agentcube-test-picod --format='{{.Size}}')\n786:     if [[ $size -gt 100000000 ]]; then\n787:         echo \"FAIL: picod image exceeds 100MB: $(numfmt --to=iec $size)\"\n788:         return 1\n789:     fi\n790:     \n791:     echo \"PASS: picod build succeeded, size: $(numfmt --to=iec $size)\"\n792:     return 0\n793: }\n794: \n795: test_binary_exists() {\n796:     local image=\"$1\"\n797:     local binary=\"$2\"\n798:     \n799:     if ! docker run --rm \"$image\" test -f \"/app/bin/$binary\"; then\n800:         echo \"FAIL: $binary not found in $image\"\n801:         return 1\n802:     fi\n803:     echo \"PASS: $binary exists in $image\"\n804:     return 0\n805: }\n806: \n807: test_user_isolation() {\n808:     local image=\"$1\"\n809:     local expected_uid=\"$2\"\n810:     \n811:     local uid=$(docker run --rm \"$image\" id -u)\n812:     if [[ \"$uid\" != \"$expected_uid\" ]]; then\n813:         echo \"FAIL: $image running as UID $uid, expected $expected_uid\"\n814:         return 1\n815:     fi\n816:     echo \"PASS: $image running as correct UID $uid\"\n817:     return 0\n818: }\n819: \n820: test_no_go_toolchain() {\n821:     local image=\"$1\"\n822:     \n823:     if docker run --rm \"$image\" which go 2>/dev/null; then\n824:         echo \"FAIL: $image contains Go toolchain\"\n825:         return 1\n826:     fi\n827:     echo \"PASS: $image does not contain Go toolchain\"\n828:     return 0\n829: }\n830: \n831: test_no_source_files() {\n832:     local image=\"$1\"\n833:     \n834:     if docker run --rm \"$image\" find /app -name \"*.go\" -type f 2>/dev/null | grep -q .; then\n835:         echo \"FAIL: $image contains Go source files\"\n836:         return 1\n837:     fi\n838:     echo \"PASS: $image does not contain Go source files\"\n839:     return 0\n840: }\n841: \n842: main() {\n843:     local failed=0\n844:     \n845:     test_workloadmanager_build || failed=1\n846:     test_router_build || failed=1\n847:     test_picod_build || failed=1\n848:     \n849:     test_binary_exists agentcube-test-workloadmanager workloadmanager || failed=1\n850:     test_binary_exists agentcube-test-router router || failed=1\n851:     test_binary_exists agentcube-test-picod picod || failed=1\n852:     \n853:     test_user_isolation agentcube-test-workloadmanager 1000 || failed=1\n854:     test_user_isolation agentcube-test-router 1000 || failed=1\n855:     test_user_isolation agentcube-test-picod 0 || failed=1\n856:     \n857:     test_no_go_toolchain agentcube-test-workloadmanager || failed=1\n858:     test_no_go_toolchain agentcube-test-router || failed=1\n859:     test_no_source_files agentcube-test-workloadmanager || failed=1\n860:     test_no_source_files agentcube-test-router || failed=1\n861:     \n862:     if [[ $failed -eq 1 ]]; then\n863:         echo \"INTEGRATION TESTS FAILED\"\n864:         exit 1\n865:     fi\n866:     \n867:     echo \"ALL INTEGRATION TESTS PASSED\"\n868:     exit 0\n869: }\n870: \n871: main\n872: ```\n873: \n874: ### E2E Tests: Kind Cluster Deployment\n875: \n876: ```bash\n877: #!/bin/bash\n878: # test_kind_deployment.sh\n879: \n880: set -euo pipefail\n881: \n882: KIND_CLUSTER_NAME=\"agentcube-test\"\n883: \n884: cleanup() {\n885:     kind delete cluster --name \"$KIND_CLUSTER_NAME\" 2>/dev/null || true\n886: }\n887: \n888: trap cleanup EXIT\n889: \n890: create_kind_cluster() {\n891:     echo \"Creating Kind cluster...\"\n892:     kind create cluster --name \"$KIND_CLUSTER_NAME\" --wait 60s\n893: }\n894: \n895: build_and_load_images() {\n896:     echo \"Building images...\"\n897:     make docker-build-all\n898:     \n899:     echo \"Loading images into Kind...\"\n900:     kind load docker-image \\\n901:         ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube/workloadmanager:latest \\\n902:         --name \"$KIND_CLUSTER_NAME\"\n903:     kind load docker-image \\\n904:         ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube/router:latest \\\n905:         --name \"$KIND_CLUSTER_NAME\"\n906:     kind load docker-image \\\n907:         ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube/picod:latest \\\n908:         --name \"$KIND_CLUSTER_NAME\"\n909: }\n910: \n911: deploy_with_helm() {\n912:     echo \"Deploying with Helm...\"\n913:     helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n914:         --namespace agentcube --create-namespace \\\n915:         --set images.workloadmanager.tag=latest \\\n916:         --set images.router.tag=latest \\\n917:         --set images.picod.tag=latest \\\n918:         --wait --timeout 300s\n919: }\n920: \n921: verify_deployments() {\n922:     echo \"Verifying deployments...\"\n923:     \n924:     local deployments=\"workloadmanager router\"\n925:     for deploy in $deployments; do\n926:         if ! kubectl rollout status deployment/$deploy -n agentcube --timeout=60s; then\n927:             echo \"FAIL: $deploy deployment not ready\"\n928:             return 1\n929:         fi\n930:         echo \"PASS: $deploy deployment ready\"\n931:     done\n932:     \n933:     return 0\n934: }\n935: \n936: verify_pods_running() {\n937:     echo \"Verifying pods...\"\n938:     \n939:     local pods=$(kubectl get pods -n agentcube -o jsonpath='{.items[*].metadata.name}')\n940:     for pod in $pods; do\n941:         local uid=$(kubectl get pod \"$pod\" -n agentcube -o jsonpath='{.spec.containers[*].securityContext.runAsUser}')\n942:         if [[ -n \"$uid\" ]]; then\n943:             echo \"Pod $pod running with securityContext.runAsUser=$uid\"\n944:         fi\n945:     done\n946:     \n947:     return 0\n948: }\n949: \n950: main() {\n951:     local failed=0\n952:     \n953:     create_kind_cluster || failed=1\n954:     build_and_load_images || failed=1\n955:     deploy_with_helm || failed=1\n956:     verify_deployments || failed=1\n957:     verify_pods_running || failed=1\n958:     \n959:     if [[ $failed -eq 1 ]]; then\n960:         echo \"E2E TESTS FAILED\"\n961:         exit 1\n962:     fi\n963:     \n964:     echo \"ALL E2E TESTS PASSED\"\n965:     exit 0\n966: }\n967: \n968: main\n969: ```\n970: \n971: ---\n972: \n973: ## File Structure\n974: \n975: | Path | Role |\n976: |------|------|\n977: | `docker/Dockerfile` | Workload Manager multi-stage build (builder → runtime) |\n978: | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | Router multi-stage build (builder → runtime) |\n979: | `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | PicoD multi-stage build (builder → runtime) |\n980: | `Makefile` | Build targets: `docker-build`, `docker-build-router`, `docker-build-picod`, `docker-build-all` |\n981: | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Helm chart image repository/tag defaults |\n982: | `.github/workflows/main.yml` | CI workflow referencing `make docker-build` |\n983: | `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml` | Release workflow for multi-arch builds |\n984: \n985: ---\n986: \n987: ## Dependencies\n988: \n989: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n990: |---------|---------|---------|\n991: | `golang:1.24-alpine` | 1.24 | Builder stage base for Go compilation |\n992: | `alpine:3.19` | 3.19 | Minimal runtime base (~5MB) |\n993: | `ubuntu:24.04` | 24.04 | Runtime base for picod (Python3 dependency) |\n994: | `ca-certificates` | latest | TLS certificate bundle |\n995: | `tzdata` | latest | Timezone data (Alpine) |\n996: | `python3` | system | Code execution dependency (Ubuntu/picod) |\n997: | `docker` | >=20.10 | BuildKit multi-stage support |\n998: | `buildx` | latest | Multi-arch cross-compilation |\n999: \n1000: ---\n1001: \n1002: ## Implementation Notes\n1003: \n1004: ### BuildKit Cache Optimization\n1005: \n1006: 1. **Go Module Cache**: Mount `/go/pkg/mod` as cache to persist module downloads across builds\n1007: 2. **Go Build Cache**: Mount `/root/.cache/go-build` to cache compiled artifacts\n1008: 3. **Cache Key**: Cache keyed by `go.mod`/`go.sum` hash for automatic invalidation\n1009: \n1010: ```dockerfile\n1011: RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/go/pkg/mod \\\n1012:     go mod download\n1013: \n1014: RUN --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache/go-build \\\n1015:     go build -ldflags=\"-w -s\" -o /app/bin/<binary> ./cmd/<module>\n1016: ```\n1017: \n1018: ### Binary Size Optimization\n1019: \n1020: | Flag | Effect |\n1021: |------|--------|\n1022: | `-w` | Strip DWARF debug information |\n1023: | `-s` | Strip symbol table |\n1024: | `CGO_ENABLED=0` | Disable CGO for static-like compilation |\n1025: | `trimpath` | Remove file system paths from binary |\n1026: \n1027: ### Security Considerations\n1028: \n1029: 1. **Non-root User**: Alpine images run as UID 1000 to reduce attack surface\n1030: 2. **Minimal Packages**: Only `ca-certificates` and `tzdata` in runtime\n1031: 3. **No Shell Required**: Binary entrypoint without shell wrapper\n1032: 4. **PicoD Exception**: Runs as root for sandbox pod management permissions\n1033: \n1034: ### Cross-Compilation\n1035: \n1036: ```bash\n1037: # amd64\n1038: docker build --build-arg TARGETOS=linux --build-arg TARGETARCH=amd64 ...\n1039: \n1040: # arm64\n1041: docker build --build-arg TARGETOS=linux --build-arg TARGETARCH=arm64 ...\n1042: \n1043: # Multi-arch with buildx\n1044: docker buildx build --platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 ...\n1045: ```\n1046: \n1047: ### CI Integration\n1048: \n1049: ```yaml\n1050: # .github/workflows/build-push-release.yml\n1051: - name: Build and push images\n1052:   run: |\n1053:     make docker-buildx-push VERSION=${{ github.ref_name }}\n1054: ```\n1055: \n1056: ---\n1057: \n1058: ## References\n1059: \n1060: - Spec: `changes/AR-032/spec.md`\n1061: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md`\n1062: - Proposal: `changes/AR-032/proposal.md`\n1063: - Tasks: `changes/AR-032/tasks.md`\n1064: - Docker multi-stage builds: https://docs.docker.com/build/building/multi-stage/\n1065: - BuildKit cache mounts: https://docs.docker.com/build/buildkit/#cache-mounts\n1066: - Go cross-compilation: https://go.dev/doc/install/source#environment\n\n(End of file - total 1066 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images) |\n| Module | `docker` |\n| Language | Dockerfile |\n| Size | S |\n| Stage | ST-1 (completed) |\n\nMulti-stage Dockerfile patterns for AgentCube's three core container images, optimizing for build separation, security, build efficiency, and consistency across workloadmanager, router, and picod images.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Architecture\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/design.md","time":{"start":1775886397826,"end":1775886397848}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886397855,"sessionID":"ses_284ec6c0effeuVBVVdzk4kiXnu","part":{"id":"prt_d7b13f162001MbCbvLB5Q2aZmn","messageID":"msg_d7b13bf0e001UrUjBp9Isrk1O8","sessionID":"ses_284ec6c0effeuVBVVdzk4kiXnu","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-1bba2d7d6f634f8c866d78be3cf856a0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-031 — RBAC 配置 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) |\n8: | Module | `manifests` |\n9: | Language | YAML |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Router RBAC Foundation (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Create Router ServiceAccount template with conditional rendering\n20:   - Purpose: Define ServiceAccount when `router.rbac.create=true`\n21:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n22:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router | grep \"kind: ServiceAccount\" | grep \"name: agentcube-router\"`\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T1.2**: Implement Router ServiceAccount validation guard\n25:   - Purpose: Fail if `router.rbac.create=true` but `router.serviceAccountName` not set\n26:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n27:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true 2>&1 | grep \"serviceAccountName must be set\"`\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T1.3**: Define Router Role with namespace-scoped secrets permissions\n30:   - Purpose: Create Role with `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` for secrets\n31:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n32:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -A10 \"kind: Role\" | grep \"secrets\"`\n33: \n34: - [ ] **T1.4**: Create Router RoleBinding to bind ServiceAccount to Role\n35:   - Purpose: Establish SA → Role binding within namespace\n36:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n37:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -A10 \"kind: RoleBinding\"`\n38: \n39: - [ ] **T1.5**: Implement Router Role namespace isolation\n40:   - Purpose: Ensure Role and RoleBinding are namespace-scoped (not cluster-wide)\n41:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n42:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa --namespace agentcube | grep \"namespace: agentcube\"`\n43: \n44: ### Phase 2: WorkloadManager RBAC (ST-2)\n45: \n46: - [ ] **T2.1**: Create WorkloadManager ServiceAccount template\n47:   - Purpose: Define ServiceAccount for WorkloadManager (cluster-scoped identity)\n48:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n49:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"kind: ServiceAccount\" | grep \"name: workloadmanager\"`\n50: \n51: - [ ] **T2.2**: Define WorkloadManager ClusterRole for agents.x-k8s.io CRDs\n52:   - Purpose: Grant permissions for `sandboxes` (full CRUD)\n53:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n54:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A15 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"sandboxes\"`\n55: \n56: - [ ] **T2.3**: Define WorkloadManager ClusterRole for extensions.agents.x-k8s.io CRDs\n57:   - Purpose: Grant permissions for `sandboxclaims`, `sandboxtemplates`, `sandboxwarmpools` and status subresource\n58:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n59:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A15 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"sandboxclaims\"`\n60: \n61: - [ ] **T2.4**: Define WorkloadManager ClusterRole for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh CRDs\n62:   - Purpose: Grant full CRUD for `codeinterpreters` + status/finalizers, read-only for `agentruntimes` + status updates\n63:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n64:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A20 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"codeinterpreters\"`\n65: \n66: - [ ] **T2.5**: Define WorkloadManager ClusterRole for core Kubernetes resources\n67:   - Purpose: Grant read-only for `pods`, full CRUD for `secrets`\n68:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n69:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A25 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"pods\"`\n70: \n71: - [ ] **T2.6**: Define WorkloadManager ClusterRole for TokenReview\n72:   - Purpose: Grant `create` permission for `authentication.k8s.io/tokenreviews`\n73:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n74:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A30 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"tokenreviews\"`\n75: \n76: - [ ] **T2.7**: Create WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding\n77:   - Purpose: Bind ClusterRole to ServiceAccount (cluster-wide binding)\n78:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n79:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A10 \"kind: ClusterRoleBinding\"`\n80: \n81: ### Phase 3: Deployment Integration (ST-3)\n82: \n83: - [ ] **T3.1**: Integrate Router ServiceAccount into Router Deployment\n84:   - Purpose: Set `serviceAccountName` in Router Deployment spec when `router.serviceAccountName` is provided\n85:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml`\n86:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep \"serviceAccountName: test-sa\"`\n87: \n88: - [ ] **T3.2**: Integrate WorkloadManager ServiceAccount into WorkloadManager Deployment\n89:   - Purpose: Set fixed `serviceAccountName: workloadmanager` in WorkloadManager Deployment\n90:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml`\n91:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A5 \"name: workloadmanager\" | grep \"serviceAccountName: workloadmanager\"`\n92: \n93: - [ ] **T3.3**: Update values.yaml with router.rbac.create configuration\n94:   - Purpose: Add `router.rbac.create: false` default and `router.serviceAccountName: \"\"` default\n95:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml`\n96:   - Verification: `grep \"rbac:\" manifests/charts/base/values.yaml && grep \"create: false\" manifests/charts/base/values.yaml`\n97: \n98: ### Phase 4: Permission Validation (ST-4)\n99: \n100: - [ ] **T4.1**: Verify Router Role has no wildcard permissions\n101:   - Purpose: Ensure no `*` in resources or verbs (least-privilege compliance)\n102:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n103:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -E 'resources:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]' | grep -E 'verbs:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]' || echo \"OK\"`\n104: \n105: - [ ] **T4.2**: Verify Router Role has no TokenReview permission\n106:   - Purpose: Router should only have secrets access (no authentication API)\n107:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n108:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -A5 \"kind: Role\" | grep \"tokenreviews\" || echo \"OK\"`\n109: \n110: - [ ] **T4.3**: Verify WorkloadManager ClusterRole has no Pod create/delete permissions\n111:   - Purpose: WorkloadManager creates pods via Sandbox CRD, not directly\n112:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n113:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A5 \"pods\" | grep -E \"(create|delete)\" || echo \"OK\"`\n114: \n115: - [ ] **T4.4**: Verify WorkloadManager ClusterRole has no AgentRuntime delete permission\n116:   - Purpose: WorkloadManager only reads AgentRuntimes, cannot delete\n117:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n118:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A5 \"agentruntimes\" | grep \"delete\" || echo \"OK\"`\n119: \n120: - [ ] **T4.5**: Verify all ClusterRole rules use correct API groups\n121:   - Purpose: Validate API groups: `agents.x-k8s.io`, `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io`, `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, `authentication.k8s.io`, core `\"\"`\n122:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n123:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A50 \"kind: ClusterRole\" | grep \"apiGroups\"`\n124: \n125: ### Phase 5: Helm Chart Validation Tests (ST-5)\n126: \n127: - [ ] **T5.1**: Run Helm lint on chart with RBAC enabled\n128:   - Purpose: Validate chart syntax with Router RBAC enabled\n129:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n130:   - Verification: `helm lint manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa`\n131: \n132: - [ ] **T5.2**: Test Router RBAC disabled scenario\n133:   - Purpose: Verify no Router RBAC resources rendered when `router.rbac.create=false`\n134:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n135:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=false | grep \"kind: Role\" || echo \"OK\"`\n136: \n137: - [ ] **T5.3**: Test Router RBAC validation guard failure\n138:   - Purpose: Verify template fails when `router.rbac.create=true` without serviceAccountName\n139:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n140:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true 2>&1 | grep \"serviceAccountName must be set\"`\n141: \n142: - [ ] **T5.4**: Test Router RBAC rendering with custom namespace\n143:   - Purpose: Verify RBAC resources use correct namespace from Helm release\n144:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n145:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa --namespace agentcube | grep \"namespace: agentcube\"`\n146: \n147: - [ ] **T5.5**: Test WorkloadManager RBAC always rendered\n148:   - Purpose: Verify WorkloadManager RBAC renders regardless of Router RBAC setting\n149:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n150:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=false | grep \"kind: ClusterRole\"`\n151: \n152: ### Phase 6: Kubernetes API Validation Tests (ST-6)\n153: \n154: - [ ] **T6.1**: Validate Router RBAC resources with kubectl dry-run\n155:   - Purpose: Verify Router RBAC YAML is valid Kubernetes schema\n156:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n157:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa > /tmp/router-rbac.yaml && kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/router-rbac.yaml | grep \"serviceaccount\"`\n158: \n159: - [ ] **T6.2**: Validate WorkloadManager RBAC resources with kubectl dry-run\n160:   - Purpose: Verify WorkloadManager RBAC YAML is valid Kubernetes schema\n161:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n162:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" > /tmp/workloadmanager-rbac.yaml && kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/workloadmanager-rbac.yaml | grep \"clusterrole\"`\n163: \n164: - [ ] **T6.3**: Validate complete chart with kubectl dry-run\n165:   - Purpose: Verify entire rendered chart is valid for Kubernetes API\n166:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/`\n167:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa > /tmp/rendered.yaml && kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/rendered.yaml`\n168: \n169: ### Phase 7: Permission Matrix Tests (ST-7)\n170: \n171: - [ ] **T7.1**: Test Router ServiceAccount can access secrets in own namespace\n172:   - Purpose: Verify `kubectl auth can-i` returns `yes` for Router SA secrets access\n173:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n174:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i get secrets --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-router -n agentcube` (expected: yes)\n175: \n176: - [ ] **T7.2**: Test Router ServiceAccount cannot access secrets in other namespace\n177:   - Purpose: Verify namespace isolation - Router SA forbidden in other namespaces\n178:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n179:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i get secrets -n other-ns --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-router` (expected: no)\n180: \n181: - [ ] **T7.3**: Test Router ServiceAccount cannot create pods\n182:   - Purpose: Verify Router has no pod creation permission\n183:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n184:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i create pods --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-router -n agentcube` (expected: no)\n185: \n186: - [ ] **T7.4**: Test WorkloadManager ServiceAccount can create sandboxes\n187:   - Purpose: Verify WorkloadManager has sandbox creation permission\n188:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n189:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i create sandboxes.agents.x-k8s.io --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (expected: yes)\n190: \n191: - [ ] **T7.5**: Test WorkloadManager ServiceAccount can create codeinterpreters\n192:   - Purpose: Verify WorkloadManager has CodeInterpreter CRD permissions\n193:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n194:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i create codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (expected: yes)\n195: \n196: - [ ] **T7.6**: Test WorkloadManager ServiceAccount cannot create pods directly\n197:   - Purpose: Verify WorkloadManager cannot create Pods (only via Sandbox CRD)\n198:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n199:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i create pods --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (expected: no)\n200: \n201: - [ ] **T7.7**: Test WorkloadManager ServiceAccount can create TokenReviews\n202:   - Purpose: Verify TokenReview create permission for authentication\n203:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n204:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i create tokenreviews.authentication.k8s.io --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (expected: yes)\n205: \n206: - [ ] **T7.8**: Test WorkloadManager ServiceAccount cannot delete AgentRuntimes\n207:   - Purpose: Verify AgentRuntime is read-only for WorkloadManager\n208:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/` (requires deployed cluster)\n209:   - Verification: `kubectl auth can-i delete agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (expected: no)\n210: \n211: ### Phase 8: Security Audit Tests (ST-8)\n212: \n213: - [ ] **T8.1**: Verify no ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding for Router\n214:   - Purpose: Router should only have namespace-scoped Role (not cluster-wide)\n215:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n216:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep \"kind: ClusterRole\" || echo \"OK\"`\n217: \n218: - [ ] **T8.2**: Verify Router Role metadata includes namespace\n219:   - Purpose: Confirm Role is namespace-scoped (not cluster-scoped)\n220:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n221:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa --namespace agentcube | grep -A3 \"kind: Role\" | grep \"namespace\"`\n222: \n223: - [ ] **T8.3**: Verify WorkloadManager ClusterRole has least-privilege verbs for pods\n224:   - Purpose: Pods should only have `get,list,watch` (no create/update/delete)\n225:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n226:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A8 \"pods\" | grep -E \"(create|update|patch|delete)\" || echo \"OK\"`\n227: \n228: - [ ] **T8.4**: Verify WorkloadManager ClusterRole has least-privilege verbs for agentruntimes\n229:   - Purpose: AgentRuntimes should only have `get,list,watch` (no create/delete)\n230:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n231:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A8 \"agentruntimes\" | grep \"verbs\" | grep -E \"(create|delete)\" || echo \"OK\"`\n232: \n233: - [ ] **T8.5**: Verify no wildcard `*` permissions in any RBAC rule\n234:   - Purpose: Security audit - wildcards violate least-privilege principle\n235:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/`\n236:   - Verification: `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -E 'verbs:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]' || echo \"OK\"`\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ## Task Dependencies\n241: \n242: ```\n243: Phase 1 (Router RBAC Foundation) ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n244: T1.1 (SA) ──┬── T1.2 (validation guard)\n245:             ├── T1.3 (Role)\n246:             ├── T1.4 (RoleBinding)\n247:             └── T1.5 (namespace isolation)\n248: \n249: Phase 2 (WorkloadManager RBAC) ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n250: T2.1 (SA) ──┬── T2.2 (agents.x-k8s.io)\n251:             ├── T2.3 (extensions.agents.x-k8s.io)\n252:             ├── T2.4 (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh)\n253:             ├── T2.5 (core resources)\n254:             ├── T2.6 (TokenReview)\n255:             └── T2.7 (ClusterRoleBinding)\n256: \n257: Phase 3 (Deployment Integration) ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n258: T1.1-T1.5 ──┬── T3.1 (Router Deployment)\n259: T2.1-T2.7 ──┬── T3.2 (WorkloadManager Deployment)\n260:             └── T3.3 (values.yaml)\n261: \n262: Phase 4 (Permission Validation) ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n263: T1.1-T3.3 ──┬── T4.1-T4.5 (permission matrix validation)\n264: \n265: Phase 5 (Helm Validation) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n266: T1.1-T4.5 ──┬── T5.1-T5.5 (Helm template tests)\n267: \n268: Phase 6 (Kubernetes API Validation) ──────────────────────────────────────────\n269: T5.1-T5.5 ──┬── T6.1-T6.3 (kubectl dry-run tests)\n270: \n271: Phase 7 (Permission Matrix Tests) ────────────────────────────────────────────\n272: T6.1-T6.3 ──┬── T7.1-T7.8 (kubectl auth can-i tests) [requires cluster]\n273: \n274: Phase 8 (Security Audit) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n275: T1.1-T7.8 ──┬── T8.1-T8.5 (security audit checks)\n276: ```\n277: \n278: ---\n279: \n280: ## Verification Commands\n281: \n282: | Task Phase | Verification Command |\n283: |------------|----------------------|\n284: | Phase 1 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -A10 \"kind: ServiceAccount\" \\| grep \"name: test-sa\"` |\n285: | Phase 2 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep -A50 \"kind: ClusterRole\" \\| grep \"sandboxes\"` |\n286: | Phase 3 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep \"serviceAccountName: test-sa\"` |\n287: | Phase 4 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa | grep -E 'verbs:\\s*\\[\"\\*\"\\]' || echo \"OK\"` |\n288: | Phase 5 | `helm lint manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=test-sa` |\n289: | Phase 6 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" > /tmp/rendered.yaml && kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f /tmp/rendered.yaml` |\n290: | Phase 7 | `kubectl auth can-i create sandboxes.agents.x-k8s.io --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workloadmanager` (requires cluster deployment) |\n291: | Phase 8 | `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"test:6379\" | grep \"kind: ClusterRole\" \\| grep -v workloadmanager || echo \"OK\"` |\n292: \n293: ---\n294: \n295: ## Acceptance Criteria\n296: \n297: - [ ] Router ServiceAccount rendered when `router.rbac.create=true`\n298: - [ ] Router Role has namespace-scoped secrets permissions (get/list/watch/create/update/patch/delete)\n299: - [ ] Router RoleBinding binds Router SA to Router Role within namespace\n300: - [ ] Router RBAC validation guard: fail if `router.rbac.create=true` without `router.serviceAccountName`\n301: - [ ] Router RBAC not rendered when `router.rbac.create=false`\n302: - [ ] Router RBAC has no cluster-scoped resources (no ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding)\n303: - [ ] Router RBAC uses correct namespace from `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n304: - [ ] WorkloadManager ServiceAccount always rendered\n305: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxes (full CRUD)\n306: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for extensions.agents.x-k8s.io (sandboxclaims, sandboxtemplates, sandboxwarmpools + status)\n307: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters (full CRUD + status/finalizers)\n308: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes (read-only + status updates)\n309: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for core pods (read-only: get/list/watch)\n310: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permissions for core secrets (full CRUD)\n311: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has permission for authentication.k8s.io/tokenreviews (create only)\n312: - [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding binds WM SA to WM ClusterRole\n313: - [ ] Router Deployment uses `router.serviceAccountName` when provided\n314: - [ ] WorkloadManager Deployment uses fixed `serviceAccountName: workloadmanager`\n315: - [ ] values.yaml includes `router.rbac.create: false` default\n316: - [ ] values.yaml includes `router.serviceAccountName: \"\"` default\n317: - [ ] Helm lint passes with 0 errors\n318: - [ ] Rendered YAML validates with kubectl dry-run\n319: - [ ] Router SA can access secrets in own namespace (kubectl auth can-i)\n320: - [ ] Router SA cannot access secrets in other namespaces (namespace isolation)\n321: - [ ] Router SA cannot create pods (least-privilege)\n322: - [ ] WorkloadManager SA can create sandboxes CRDs\n323: - [ ] WorkloadManager SA can create codeinterpreter CRDs\n324: - [ ] WorkloadManager SA cannot create pods directly (only via Sandbox)\n325: - [ ] WorkloadManager SA cannot delete agentruntimes (read-only)\n326: - [ ] WorkloadManager SA can create TokenReviews\n327: - [ ] No wildcard `*` permissions in any RBAC rule\n328: - [ ] Router Role has no TokenReview permission\n329: - [ ] All RBAC rules use correct API groups\n330: \n331: ---\n332: \n333: ## File Changes Summary\n334: \n335: | File | Action | Lines | Description |\n336: |------|--------|-------|-------------|\n337: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | Create | 49 | Router RBAC (ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding - conditional rendering) |\n338: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | Create | 131 | WorkloadManager RBAC (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding) |\n339: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` | Modify | 81 | Add serviceAccountName field integration |\n340: | `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` | Modify | - | Add serviceAccountName: workloadmanager (if missing) |\n341: | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Modify | 57 | Add router.rbac.create and router.serviceAccountName defaults |\n342: \n343: ---\n344: \n345: ## Implementation Notes\n346: \n347: ### Router RBAC Conditional Rendering Pattern\n348: \n349: ```yaml\n350: {{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}\n351: {{- if not .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n352: {{- fail \"router.serviceAccountName must be set when router.rbac.create is true\" }}\n353: {{- end }}\n354: apiVersion: v1\n355: kind: ServiceAccount\n356: metadata:\n357:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n358:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n359:   labels:\n360:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n361: ---\n362: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n363: kind: Role\n364: metadata:\n365:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n366:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n367:   labels:\n368:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n369: rules:\n370:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n371:     resources: [\"secrets\"]\n372:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n373: ---\n374: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n375: kind: RoleBinding\n376: metadata:\n377:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n378:   namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n379:   labels:\n380:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n381: roleRef:\n382:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n383:   kind: Role\n384:   name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n385: subjects:\n386:   - kind: ServiceAccount\n387:     name: {{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}\n388:     namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\n389: {{- end }}\n390: ```\n391: \n392: ### WorkloadManager ClusterRole Permission Matrix\n393: \n394: ```yaml\n395: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n396: kind: ClusterRole\n397: metadata:\n398:   name: workloadmanager\n399: rules:\n400:   - apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n401:     resources: [\"sandboxes\"]\n402:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n403:   \n404:   - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n405:     resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]\n406:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n407:   \n408:   - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n409:     resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]\n410:     verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n411:   \n412:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n413:     resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]\n414:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n415:   \n416:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n417:     resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\", \"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]\n418:     verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n419:   \n420:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n421:     resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]\n422:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n423:   \n424:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n425:     resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]\n426:     verbs: [\"update\", \"patch\"]\n427:   \n428:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n429:     resources: [\"pods\"]\n430:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n431:   \n432:   - apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]\n433:     resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]\n434:     verbs: [\"create\"]\n435:   \n436:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n437:     resources: [\"secrets\"]\n438:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n439: ```\n440: \n441: ### RBAC Scope Design Rationale\n442: \n443: | Component | Scope | Reason |\n444: |-----------|-------|--------|\n445: | Router | Namespace-scoped (Role/RoleBinding) | Router only manages secrets in its namespace (JWT signing keys, identity secrets). No cluster-wide access needed. |\n446: | WorkloadManager | Cluster-scoped (ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding) | Agent-sandbox CRDs are cluster-scoped; WorkloadManager manages sandboxes across namespaces. Cross-namespace sandbox lifecycle management requires cluster-wide permissions. |\n447: \n448: ### Least Privilege Principles\n449: \n450: | Resource | Verbs | Reason |\n451: |----------|-------|--------|\n452: | pods | get, list, watch | Read-only monitoring; WorkloadManager creates pods via Sandbox CRD, not directly |\n453: | agentruntimes | get, list, watch | Read-only reference; WorkloadManager references AgentRuntimes but does not manage lifecycle |\n454: | agentruntimes/status | update, patch | Status updates only; no delete permission |\n455: | sandboxwarmpools/status | get, update, patch | Status subresource pattern; separate from main resource CRUD |\n456: | codeinterpreters/finalizers | update | Finalizer management only; limited to finalizer operations |\n457: | tokenreviews | create | One-shot authentication; no read/delete (ephemeral operation) |\n458: \n459: ---\n460: \n461: ## Implementation Timeline\n462: \n463: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n464: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n465: | Phase 1: Router RBAC Foundation | T1.1-T1.5 | Completed | 100% |\n466: | Phase 2: WorkloadManager RBAC | T2.1-T2.7 | Completed | 100% |\n467: | Phase 3: Deployment Integration | T3.1-T3.3 | Completed | 100% |\n468: | Phase 4: Permission Validation | T4.1-T4.5 | Pending | 0% |\n469: | Phase 5: Helm Validation | T5.1-T5.5 | Pending | 0% |\n470: | Phase 6: Kubernetes API Validation | T6.1-T6.3 | Pending | 0% |\n471: | Phase 7: Permission Matrix Tests | T7.1-T7.8 | Pending | 0% |\n472: | Phase 8: Security Audit | T8.1-T8.5 | Pending | 0% |\n473: \n474: **Total Progress: 30% Complete (15/50 tasks)**\n475: \n476: ---\n477: \n478: ## References\n479: \n480: - Design: `changes/AR-031/design.md`\n481: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md`\n482: - Proposal: `changes/AR-031/proposal.md`\n483: - AR-030 Helm Chart Design: `changes/AR-030/design.md` (RBAC template patterns)\n484: - Kubernetes RBAC Documentation: https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/access-authn-authz/rbac/\n485: - Kubernetes API Reference: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n486: - Helm Template Functions: https://helm.sh/docs/chart_template_guide/function_list/\n487: - agent-sandbox CRDs: https://sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox\n\n(End of file - total 487 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-031 — RBAC 配置 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) |\n| Module | `manifests` |\n| Language | YAML |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Router RBAC Foundation (ST-1)\n\n- [ ] **T1.1**: Create Router ServiceAccount template with conditional rendering\n  - Purpose: Define ServiceAccount when `router.rbac.create=true`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-031/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775886397828,"end":1775886397852}}}}
